The paper deals with a graph partitioning problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The problem involves partitioning nodes into clusters to minimize inter-cluster communication and migration cost. This problem has connections to other well-known online problems such as online paging and maximum matching. Therefore, the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.AL (Computational Geometry), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
